<main class="stanford-masthead" id="content"
  style="background-image: url(<%= asset_path 'splash.jpg' %>); background-position: center; ">
  <div class="container flex-wrap flex-md-nowrap">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h1 class="me-auto"><span class="stanford">Stanford</span><span class="digital-repo">Digital Repository</span></h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="fs-4">Long term preservation of scholarly works at Stanford</p>
    <div class="text-center text-md-left way-down">
      <h2>Go to the SDR Dashboard</h2>
      <h3 class="mb-4">to create or manage deposits</h3>
      <%= link_to dashboard_path, class: 'btn btn-primary btn-xl mb-3 mr-md-3' do %>
        <span class="me-5">Enter here</span><span class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right ml-2" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <% end %>
      <%= render PageContentComponent.new(page_content: @page_content) %>
    </div>
    <a href="#photo-credit" class="credit">Photo credit<sup>*</sup></a>
  </div>
</main>
<div class="benefits">
  <div class="container p-5">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3>The process is simple</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Describe your work and upload your file(s).</li>
          <li>Choose a license and access settings.</li>
          <li>Click "Deposit" to submit.</li>
        </ol>
        <%= link_to('Learn more about SDR Services', Settings.sdr_url,
                    class: 'btn') %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3>Small effort for large payoff</h3>
        <ul class="fa-ul">
          <li><span class="fa-li" aria-hidden="true"><span class="fa-solid fa-check"></span></span>Persistent link for sharing your content</li>
          <li><span class="fa-li" aria-hidden="true"><span class="fa-solid fa-check"></span></span>Preserved by the Libraries</li>
          <li><span class="fa-li" aria-hidden="true"><span class="fa-solid fa-check"></span></span>Discoverable by all via SearchWorks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card news">
          <div class="text-center">
            <%= image_tag 'home_news.jpg', height: 54, width: 185, alt: 'News' %>

            <h3 class="fs-5 mt-3">Latest SDR news</h3>
          </div>

          <form action="https://stanford.us20.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=139e1b2d3df8f8cacd77c8160&amp;id=4f4148a871"
            method="post" data-turbo="false" id="mc-embedded-subscribe-form"
            name="mc-embedded-subscribe-form" class="validate" target="_blank" novalidate>
        	   <label for="mce-EMAIL">Sign up for our newsletter</label>
             <div class="row">
               <div class="col-sm-9">
        	      <input type="email" value="" name="EMAIL" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="mce-EMAIL" placeholder="Enter your email address" required>
             <!-- real people should not fill this in and expect good things - do not remove this or risk form bot signups-->
                <div style="position: absolute; left: -5000px;" aria-hidden="true"><input type="text" name="b_139e1b2d3df8f8cacd77c8160_4f4148a871" tabindex="-1" value=""></div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-3">
                  <input type="submit" value="Subscribe" name="subscribe" id="mc-embedded-subscribe" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">
                </div>
             </div>
          </form>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="whys">
  <div class="container p-4">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= image_tag 'home_who.jpg', height: 80, width: 80, aria: { hidden: true } %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= image_tag 'home_what.jpg', height: 80, width: 80, aria: { hidden: true } %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= image_tag 'home_why.jpg', height: 88, width: 80, aria: { hidden: true } %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= image_tag 'home_when.jpg', height: 80, width: 80, aria: { hidden: true } %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row text-row">
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Who can deposit?</h3>
        <p>Members of the Stanford community:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Students</li>
          <li>Faculty</li>
          <li>Postdocs</li>
          <li>Staff</li>
        </ul>


      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>What can I deposit?</h3>
        <p>Material of scholarly value:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Research data in any format, including data for publications</li>
          <li>Articles, working paper, pre-prints, technical reports, etc</li>
          <li>Student works, such as honors theses and course research projects</li>
          <li>Artistic works</li>
          <li>Conference materials, like slides and posters</li>
          <li>Archival documents, recordings, oral histories, etc.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Why should I deposit?</h3>

        <p>Features of SDR:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Shareable, persistent link for citing your work</li>
          <li>Findable in SearchWorks, the library catalog, which is crawled by Google</li>
          <li>Easily shareable via social media and embeddable in other websites</li>
          <li>Available to the world or just Stanford -- you decide!</li>
          <li>Embargos available up to 3 years </li>
          <li>Your choice of licenses</li>
          <li>Digital preservation by Stanford Libraries</li>
          <li>DOIs also available</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>When should I deposit?</h3>

        <p>Deposit your works:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>When they are complete and ready to share</li>
          <li>To accompany an article at the time of the article's publication</li>
          <li>To fulfill the sharing requirements of a grant</li>
          <li>Before you or your colleagues move on from Stanford</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The SDR is not designed as working space or backup storage.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col footnote" id="photo-credit">
        *Visualization Lab of SLACâ€™s Kavli Institute for Particle Astrophysics
        and Cosmology (KIPAC). Dwarf Galaxy animation. 3-D videos, created from
        actual data, show the origins of the universe. Credit: Linda A. Cicero
        and Steve Fyffe / Stanford News Service; Kavli Institute for Particle
        Astrophysics and Cosmology May 30, 2012
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
